  title: Why do we use events to trigger sound effects instead of calling audio methods
    directly in gameplay scripts?
  text: Events allow for clean decoupling. The gameplay logic only needs to raise
    an event, and the SoundManager listens and handles the audio. This keeps your
    game flexible, modular, and easier to maintain or scale.
